snippet.textDisplay:
Falun Gong practitioners held an all-day activity in London's Chinatown on Saturday, February 1, 2020.

They demonstrated the Falun Gong exercises, distributed fliers and collected signatures for a petition asking the UK government to help end the human rights abuses in China. They explained to people about the benefits of practicing Falun Gong and explained the campaign by the Chinese Communist Party (CCP) of the persecution against practitioners in China.




Falun Gong practitioners demonstrated the exercises, distributed fliers, and talked to the public about the persecution in London's Chinatown.



Awareness-raising efforts continue into the evening.

Susan and her husband Ian are from Cambridge and were visiting London. They paused to watch practitioners do the Falun Gong exercises and read the information boards.

snippet.textDisplay:
I work for Uber Eats as a bicycle courier in London Central and McDonald's staff hold us to moral ransom by asking "Start the job first before we give you the order." I always say "No because I don't work for McDonald's and you're not my supervisor." I have spoken to Uber Eats about this and they have no control over the situation. They have also confirmed that it's not mandatory procedure for the courier to start the delivery first in order to receive the order from the merchant.

It's my understanding that McDonald's have a policy to refuse to honour their side of the contract between themselves and Uber Eats by refusing to allow us to have autonomy over our own responsibility. So this video is a far cry from the toxic environment of suspicion and resentment that we often find ourselves immersed in......
